04658nam a2200661Ia 9780231558792DE-B159720240602123719.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||240602t20232023nyu    fo  d z      eng d  a2023024116  a97802315587927 a10.7312/sama211202doi  a(DE-B1597)673034  a(OCoLC)1410929428  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  anyucUS-NY00aPN56.A43bS26 2023 4aPN56.A43bS26 2023 7aLIT0060002bisacsh04a801/.9223/eng/202307281 aSamatar, Sofia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aTone /cKate Zambreno, Sofia Samatar. 1aNew York, NY : bColumbia University Press, c[2023] 4c©2023  a1 online resource  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tI. Front Matter, or The Zone of Our Mutual Sensitivity -- tII. Fog, or A Gradual Accumulation -- tIII. The Wasteland, or Our Own Colorless Patch of Sky -- tIV. Hoard, or An Unaired Room -- tV. Aviary, or Animal -- tVI. Guest Lecture, or Reports to an Academy -- tVII. Lighted Window, or Studies in Atmosphere -- tAcknowledgments -- tNotes0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aTone is a collaborative study of literary tone, a notoriously challenging and slippery topic for criticism. Both granular and global, infusing a text with feeling, tone is so difficult to pin down that responses to it often take the vague form of “I know it when I see it.”In Tone, a cooperative authorial voice under the name of the Committee to Investigate Atmosphere begins from the premise that tone is relational, belonging to shared experience rather than a single author, and should be approached through a communal practice. In partnership, the Committee explores the atmospheres emanating from texts by Nella Larsen, W. G. Sebald, Heike Geissler, Hiroko Oyamada, Mieko Kanai, Bhanu Kapil, Franz Kafka, Renee Gladman, and others, attending to the chafing of political irritation, the hunger of precarious and temporary work, and the lonely delights of urban and suburban walks.This study treats a variety of questions: How is tone filtered through translation? Can a text hold the feelings that pass between humans and animals? What can attention to literary tone reveal about shared spaces such as factories, universities, and streets and the clashes and connections that happen there? Searching and conversational, Tone seeks immersion in literary affect to convey the experience of reading—and living—together.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aAffect (Psychology) in literature. 0aAuthors and readers. 0aDiscourse analysis, Literary. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Semiotics & Theory.2bisacsh1 aZambreno, Kate, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812740uhttps://doi.org/10.7312/sama2112040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780231558792423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780231558792/original  a978-3-11-074967-0  Columbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DG